{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013U2Ym3WioGMfb3BEf8a2v8","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have all the information you need. Here's the exact response shape for both endpoints:\n\n## GET /profile/transactions\n\n**Response shape:**\n```typescript\n{\n  transactions: Array<{\n    id: string;\n    game: string;  // mapped: \"coinflip\" | \"lord-of-rngs\" | \"close-call\"\n    matchId: string;\n    event: \"join\" | \"win\" | \"loss\" | \"refund\";\n    amountLamports: string;  // string representation of number\n    txSig: string | null;\n    createdAt: string;  // ISO8601 datetime string\n  }>;\n  nextCursor: string | null;  // pagination cursor (the id of last transaction if more exist)\n}\n```\n\n**Pagination**: The endpoint accepts query params:\n- `cursor` (optional): id of last transaction from previous page\n- `limit` (optional): max 50, default 20\n- `game` (optional): filter by game (\"coinflip\", \"lord-of-rngs\", \"close-call\", or DB names \"lord\", \"closecall\")\n\n**Query example**: `GET /profile/transactions?limit=10&game=coinflip&cursor=abc123`\n\n---\n\n## GET /price/sol-usd\n\n**Response shape:**\n```typescript\n{\n  price: number;      // e.g., 195.42 (computed as raw_price * 10^expo)\n  expo: number;       // exponent (typically negative, e.g., -8)\n  updatedAt: string;  // ISO8601 datetime when Pyth published this price\n}\n```\n\n**Error response (503 if price unavailable)**:\n```typescript\n{\n  error: \"Price unavailable\"\n}\n```\n\n**Details**:\n- Uses Pyth Hermes client with 60-second cache TTL\n- Feed ID: `0xef0d8b6fda2ceba41da15d4095d1da392a0d2f8ed0c6c7bc0f4cfac8c280b56d` (SOL/USD, same on mainnet + devnet)\n- Returns stale cache on error rather than failing hard\n\n---\n\n## Key Notes\n\n1. **amountLamports is a string** (not a number) in the transactions response—this is intentional to avoid JavaScript number precision loss.\n2. **Game name mapping**: The response maps DB names (`coinflip`, `lord`, `closecall`) to frontend names (`coinflip`, `lord-of-rngs`, `close-call`).\n3. **Cursor pagination**: Use the `id` of the last transaction from the previous response as `cursor` for the next page."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a16a28cc35e911f47 (use SendMessage with to: 'a16a28cc35e911f47' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 41848\ntool_uses: 3\nduration_ms: 10218</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6352b9d5-eba7-498a-a945-ee2c953d2486","uuid":"3f0e9d4a-7986-474c-9161-c90de3a58380","timestamp":"2026-03-19T19:01:24.689Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read the following files to understand the backend API shape and how the profile route works:\n1. /workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/profile.ts\n2. /workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/price.ts\n3. /workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db.ts (just the getUserTransactions function and UserTransaction type)\n\nI need to understand the exact response shape of GET /profile/transactions and GET /price/sol-usd.","agentId":"a16a28cc35e911f47","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have all the information you need. Here's the exact response shape for both endpoints:\n\n## GET /profile/transactions\n\n**Response shape:**\n```typescript\n{\n  transactions: Array<{\n    id: string;\n    game: string;  // mapped: \"coinflip\" | \"lord-of-rngs\" | \"close-call\"\n    matchId: string;\n    event: \"join\" | \"win\" | \"loss\" | \"refund\";\n    amountLamports: string;  // string representation of number\n    txSig: string | null;\n    createdAt: string;  // ISO8601 datetime string\n  }>;\n  nextCursor: string | null;  // pagination cursor (the id of last transaction if more exist)\n}\n```\n\n**Pagination**: The endpoint accepts query params:\n- `cursor` (optional): id of last transaction from previous page\n- `limit` (optional): max 50, default 20\n- `game` (optional): filter by game (\"coinflip\", \"lord-of-rngs\", \"close-call\", or DB names \"lord\", \"closecall\")\n\n**Query example**: `GET /profile/transactions?limit=10&game=coinflip&cursor=abc123`\n\n---\n\n## GET /price/sol-usd\n\n**Response shape:**\n```typescript\n{\n  price: number;      // e.g., 195.42 (computed as raw_price * 10^expo)\n  expo: number;       // exponent (typically negative, e.g., -8)\n  updatedAt: string;  // ISO8601 datetime when Pyth published this price\n}\n```\n\n**Error response (503 if price unavailable)**:\n```typescript\n{\n  error: \"Price unavailable\"\n}\n```\n\n**Details**:\n- Uses Pyth Hermes client with 60-second cache TTL\n- Feed ID: `0xef0d8b6fda2ceba41da15d4095d1da392a0d2f8ed0c6c7bc0f4cfac8c280b56d` (SOL/USD, same on mainnet + devnet)\n- Returns stale cache on error rather than failing hard\n\n---\n\n## Key Notes\n\n1. **amountLamports is a string** (not a number) in the transactions response—this is intentional to avoid JavaScript number precision loss.\n2. **Game name mapping**: The response maps DB names (`coinflip`, `lord`, `closecall`) to frontend names (`coinflip`, `lord-of-rngs`, `close-call`).\n3. **Cursor pagination**: Use the `id` of the last transaction from the previous response as `cursor` for the next page."}],"totalDurationMs":10218,"totalTokens":41848,"totalToolUseCount":3,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":11737,"cache_read_input_tokens":29459,"output_tokens":645,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":11737},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
