{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FhDjN8ZwAxzsVHRaG5YiMb","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me compile a comprehensive summary of the player-profile feature directory.\n\n## Comprehensive Player-Profile Feature Directory Overview\n\n### Directory Structure\nAll files are located in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/player-profile/`\n\n### 1. **ProfileTransaction Type (types.ts)**\n\n**ProfileTransaction Interface:**\n```typescript\ninterface ProfileTransaction {\n  id: string;\n  timestamp: number;\n  gameId: GameId;\n  matchId: string;\n  wagerAmount: number;\n  outcome: \"win\" | \"loss\";\n  payoutAmount: number;\n  netResult: number; // positive for wins, negative for losses\n}\n```\n\nRelated types:\n- **GameId**: \"coinflip\" | \"lord-of-rngs\" | \"crypto-crash\" | \"close-call\" | \"game-of-trades\"\n- **GAME_NAMES**: Record mapping GameId to display names\n\n### 2. **ProfileTransactions Component (ProfileTransactions.tsx)**\n\n**Current Implementation:**\n- Uses `useMemo` hook to fetch transactions via `getTransactions(address, 50)`\n- Displays a table with columns: Time, Game, Wager, Outcome, Payout, Net\n- Shows relative timestamps (e.g., \"5m ago\", \"2h ago\")\n- Color-coded outcome and net result indicators\n- Empty state: \"No transactions yet. Start playing to build your history!\"\n\n**Data Flow:**\n```\nProfileTransactions (address) \n  → getTransactions(address, 50) [from mock-simulation]\n  → ProfileTransaction[]\n  → Render table\n```\n\n### 3. **Mock Data Generation (mock-simulation.ts)**\n\n**Store Structure:**\n- `profiles`: Map<string, PlayerProfile>\n- `transactions`: Map<string, ProfileTransaction[]>\n- `profileListeners`: Set of update callbacks\n\n**Key Functions for Transactions:**\n- `recordTransaction(event: GameResultEvent)`: Creates and stores transactions\n  - Keeps only last 100 transactions per player\n  - Stores most recent first (unshift pattern)\n  - Generates unique ID: `tx-${Date.now()}-${random}`\n  - Calculates `netResult = outcome === \"win\" ? payoutAmount - wagerAmount : -wagerAmount`\n\n- `getTransactions(address: string, limit = 50)`: Returns transactions up to limit\n\n**Transaction Recording Flow:**\n```\nrecordGameResult(event) \n  → calculates XP & updates stats\n  → recordTransaction(event)\n    → creates ProfileTransaction\n    → stores in transactions map\n```\n\n**Mock Profile Generation:**\n- Generates 8 demo players with realistic profiles on initialization\n- Assigns random levels (weighted distribution: 50% L1-15, 30% L16-40, 15% L41-70, 5% L71-100)\n- Creates random usernames from adjectives + nouns + numbers\n- Generates random avatars unlocked for their level\n- Creates random stats based on level\n\n### 4. **Data Fetching Patterns**\n\n**Pattern 1: Direct Store Access (Current)**\n- Component calls `getTransactions(address)` directly in `useMemo`\n- No async/await needed for mock data\n- Data stored entirely in-memory per session\n\n**Pattern 2: Event-Based Updates**\n- `profileEventBus.subscribe()` in context listens for game results\n- When game completes, `emitGameResult()` calls are triggered\n- Profile context records the event via `recordGameResult()`\n- Listeners notified and UI re-renders\n\n**Pattern 3: Profile Subscriptions**\n```typescript\nsubscribeToProfiles(callback) → returns unsubscribe function\n// Used in PlayerProfileContext to sync profile updates\n```\n\n### 5. **Profile Context (PlayerProfileContext.tsx)**\n\n**Key Features:**\n- Loads/creates profile when wallet connects\n- Forces level 100 for connected wallet (testing purposes): `getOrCreateProfile(address, 100)`\n- Subscribes to game result events via `profileEventBus`\n- Provides context API for all profile operations\n\n**Context Value Type:**\n```typescript\ninterface PlayerProfileContextValue {\n  myProfile: PlayerProfile | null;\n  loading: boolean;\n  getProfile: (address: string) => PlayerProfile | null;\n  loadProfile: (address: string) => Promise<PlayerProfile | null>;\n  updateUsername: (username: string) => Promise<void>;\n  updateAvatar: (avatarId: AvatarId) => Promise<void>;\n  connectDiscord/Twitter: () => Promise<void>;\n  claimLoot/claimAllLoot: () => Promise<number>;\n  selectedProfileAddress: string | null;\n  openMiniProfile/closeMiniProfile: (address: string) => void;\n  getDisplayName/getAvatarId/getBorderStyle: (address: string | level) => string | AvatarId | BorderStyle;\n  isAvatarUnlocked: (avatarId: AvatarId, level: number) => boolean;\n}\n```\n\n### 6. **Profile Page (ProfilePage.tsx)**\n\n**Tab Structure:**\n- **Stats**: Displays `ProfileStats` component\n- **Transactions**: Displays `ProfileTransactions` component\n- **Settings**: Displays `ProfileSettings` component\n\n**Features:**\n- Editable username with real-time validation\n- Avatar change via `AvatarSelectorModal`\n- RNG Buff indicator (from boss-raid integration)\n- Level progress bar\n- Username validation: 3-20 chars, alphanumeric + underscores\n\n### 7. **Profile Stats Component (ProfileStats.tsx)**\n\n**Displays:**\n- Aggregate stats in grid: Games Played, Total Wagered, Total Wins, Net Profit, Win Rate, Best Streak\n- Per-game breakdown table with columns: Game Name, # Games, W/L, Win %, Amount Wagered\n\n### 8. **XP Calculator (xp-calculator.ts)**\n\n**Key Formulas:**\n- XP for level: `50 * level² + 50 * level`\n- Base XP per SOL wagered: 100 XP\n- Win bonus multiplier: 50% extra\n- Total game XP: `calculateWagerXP(wager) + (won ? calculateWinBonusXP(wager) : 0)`\n\n### 9. **Profile Event Bus (profile-event-bus.ts)**\n\n**Architecture:**\n- Singleton event emitter pattern\n- Games emit via `emitGameResult()` or specialized functions:\n  - `emitCoinflipResults()`: winner + loser\n  - `emitLordOfRngsResults()`: all participants\n  - `emitCryptoCrashResults()`: array of results\n  - `emitCloseCallResults()`: array of results\n\n**Usage:**\n```typescript\nemitGameResult(gameId, matchId, playerAddress, wagerAmount, outcome, payoutAmount)\n→ profileEventBus.emit(event)\n→ notifies all listeners\n```\n\n### 10. **Public Exports (index.ts)**\n\n**Components Exported:**\n- PlayerAvatar, PlayerAvatarCompact, LevelProgressBar, MiniProfileModal, ProfilePage, AvatarSelector\n\n**Hooks/Context:**\n- PlayerProfileProvider, usePlayerProfile, truncateAddress\n\n**Types:**\n- All major types (PlayerProfile, ProfileTransaction, GameId, etc.)\n\n**Utilities:**\n- XP calculator functions\n- Event bus functions\n- Mock simulation helpers (for testing/development)\n\n### 11. **Mock Simulation Public API**\n\nExported utilities for testing:\n- `getProfile(address)`: Retrieve stored profile\n- `getOrCreateProfile(address, forceLevel?)`: Get or create with optional level override\n- `getTransactions(address, limit)`: Get transaction history\n- `getDisplayName(address)`: Get or generate username\n- `getAvatarId(address)`: Get assigned avatar\n- `getLevel(address)`: Get player level\n- `addLoot(address, source, amount, description, gameId?, matchId?, expiresAt?)`: Award loot\n- `clearAllProfiles()`: Reset store (testing)\n- `getAllProfiles()`: Debug helper\n\n### Summary\n\nThe player-profile feature is a **complete mock-based system** that:\n1. **Stores profiles and transactions in-memory** with Maps and subscription pattern\n2. **Uses ProfileTransaction type** to track game history with outcomes and net results\n3. **Integrates with games via event bus** - games emit results, profile system records them\n4. **Provides React context API** for app-wide profile access\n5. **Includes UI components** for display (transactions table, stats grid, settings)\n6. **Auto-generates realistic mock data** for demo purposes\n7. **Uses XP formulas** to calculate levels and progression\n8. **Currently all mock** - no backend integration yet (simulated 100-300ms delays on mutations)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a408058893b8e0c1a (use SendMessage with to: 'a408058893b8e0c1a' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 64310\ntool_uses: 13\nduration_ms: 57137</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6352b9d5-eba7-498a-a945-ee2c953d2486","uuid":"6f2f0576-92b9-4cdb-834a-244a7947c966","timestamp":"2026-03-19T19:02:04.088Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the player-profile feature directory thoroughly. I need to understand:\n1. The ProfileTransactions component and how it currently works with mocks\n2. The types.ts file with ProfileTransaction type\n3. Any existing hooks or data fetching patterns\n4. The mock data generation\n5. All files in `apps/platform/src/features/player-profile/`\n\nRead ALL files in this directory. Base path: /workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/player-profile/\n\nAlso check for any index exports from this directory.","agentId":"a408058893b8e0c1a","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me compile a comprehensive summary of the player-profile feature directory.\n\n## Comprehensive Player-Profile Feature Directory Overview\n\n### Directory Structure\nAll files are located in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/player-profile/`\n\n### 1. **ProfileTransaction Type (types.ts)**\n\n**ProfileTransaction Interface:**\n```typescript\ninterface ProfileTransaction {\n  id: string;\n  timestamp: number;\n  gameId: GameId;\n  matchId: string;\n  wagerAmount: number;\n  outcome: \"win\" | \"loss\";\n  payoutAmount: number;\n  netResult: number; // positive for wins, negative for losses\n}\n```\n\nRelated types:\n- **GameId**: \"coinflip\" | \"lord-of-rngs\" | \"crypto-crash\" | \"close-call\" | \"game-of-trades\"\n- **GAME_NAMES**: Record mapping GameId to display names\n\n### 2. **ProfileTransactions Component (ProfileTransactions.tsx)**\n\n**Current Implementation:**\n- Uses `useMemo` hook to fetch transactions via `getTransactions(address, 50)`\n- Displays a table with columns: Time, Game, Wager, Outcome, Payout, Net\n- Shows relative timestamps (e.g., \"5m ago\", \"2h ago\")\n- Color-coded outcome and net result indicators\n- Empty state: \"No transactions yet. Start playing to build your history!\"\n\n**Data Flow:**\n```\nProfileTransactions (address) \n  → getTransactions(address, 50) [from mock-simulation]\n  → ProfileTransaction[]\n  → Render table\n```\n\n### 3. **Mock Data Generation (mock-simulation.ts)**\n\n**Store Structure:**\n- `profiles`: Map<string, PlayerProfile>\n- `transactions`: Map<string, ProfileTransaction[]>\n- `profileListeners`: Set of update callbacks\n\n**Key Functions for Transactions:**\n- `recordTransaction(event: GameResultEvent)`: Creates and stores transactions\n  - Keeps only last 100 transactions per player\n  - Stores most recent first (unshift pattern)\n  - Generates unique ID: `tx-${Date.now()}-${random}`\n  - Calculates `netResult = outcome === \"win\" ? payoutAmount - wagerAmount : -wagerAmount`\n\n- `getTransactions(address: string, limit = 50)`: Returns transactions up to limit\n\n**Transaction Recording Flow:**\n```\nrecordGameResult(event) \n  → calculates XP & updates stats\n  → recordTransaction(event)\n    → creates ProfileTransaction\n    → stores in transactions map\n```\n\n**Mock Profile Generation:**\n- Generates 8 demo players with realistic profiles on initialization\n- Assigns random levels (weighted distribution: 50% L1-15, 30% L16-40, 15% L41-70, 5% L71-100)\n- Creates random usernames from adjectives + nouns + numbers\n- Generates random avatars unlocked for their level\n- Creates random stats based on level\n\n### 4. **Data Fetching Patterns**\n\n**Pattern 1: Direct Store Access (Current)**\n- Component calls `getTransactions(address)` directly in `useMemo`\n- No async/await needed for mock data\n- Data stored entirely in-memory per session\n\n**Pattern 2: Event-Based Updates**\n- `profileEventBus.subscribe()` in context listens for game results\n- When game completes, `emitGameResult()` calls are triggered\n- Profile context records the event via `recordGameResult()`\n- Listeners notified and UI re-renders\n\n**Pattern 3: Profile Subscriptions**\n```typescript\nsubscribeToProfiles(callback) → returns unsubscribe function\n// Used in PlayerProfileContext to sync profile updates\n```\n\n### 5. **Profile Context (PlayerProfileContext.tsx)**\n\n**Key Features:**\n- Loads/creates profile when wallet connects\n- Forces level 100 for connected wallet (testing purposes): `getOrCreateProfile(address, 100)`\n- Subscribes to game result events via `profileEventBus`\n- Provides context API for all profile operations\n\n**Context Value Type:**\n```typescript\ninterface PlayerProfileContextValue {\n  myProfile: PlayerProfile | null;\n  loading: boolean;\n  getProfile: (address: string) => PlayerProfile | null;\n  loadProfile: (address: string) => Promise<PlayerProfile | null>;\n  updateUsername: (username: string) => Promise<void>;\n  updateAvatar: (avatarId: AvatarId) => Promise<void>;\n  connectDiscord/Twitter: () => Promise<void>;\n  claimLoot/claimAllLoot: () => Promise<number>;\n  selectedProfileAddress: string | null;\n  openMiniProfile/closeMiniProfile: (address: string) => void;\n  getDisplayName/getAvatarId/getBorderStyle: (address: string | level) => string | AvatarId | BorderStyle;\n  isAvatarUnlocked: (avatarId: AvatarId, level: number) => boolean;\n}\n```\n\n### 6. **Profile Page (ProfilePage.tsx)**\n\n**Tab Structure:**\n- **Stats**: Displays `ProfileStats` component\n- **Transactions**: Displays `ProfileTransactions` component\n- **Settings**: Displays `ProfileSettings` component\n\n**Features:**\n- Editable username with real-time validation\n- Avatar change via `AvatarSelectorModal`\n- RNG Buff indicator (from boss-raid integration)\n- Level progress bar\n- Username validation: 3-20 chars, alphanumeric + underscores\n\n### 7. **Profile Stats Component (ProfileStats.tsx)**\n\n**Displays:**\n- Aggregate stats in grid: Games Played, Total Wagered, Total Wins, Net Profit, Win Rate, Best Streak\n- Per-game breakdown table with columns: Game Name, # Games, W/L, Win %, Amount Wagered\n\n### 8. **XP Calculator (xp-calculator.ts)**\n\n**Key Formulas:**\n- XP for level: `50 * level² + 50 * level`\n- Base XP per SOL wagered: 100 XP\n- Win bonus multiplier: 50% extra\n- Total game XP: `calculateWagerXP(wager) + (won ? calculateWinBonusXP(wager) : 0)`\n\n### 9. **Profile Event Bus (profile-event-bus.ts)**\n\n**Architecture:**\n- Singleton event emitter pattern\n- Games emit via `emitGameResult()` or specialized functions:\n  - `emitCoinflipResults()`: winner + loser\n  - `emitLordOfRngsResults()`: all participants\n  - `emitCryptoCrashResults()`: array of results\n  - `emitCloseCallResults()`: array of results\n\n**Usage:**\n```typescript\nemitGameResult(gameId, matchId, playerAddress, wagerAmount, outcome, payoutAmount)\n→ profileEventBus.emit(event)\n→ notifies all listeners\n```\n\n### 10. **Public Exports (index.ts)**\n\n**Components Exported:**\n- PlayerAvatar, PlayerAvatarCompact, LevelProgressBar, MiniProfileModal, ProfilePage, AvatarSelector\n\n**Hooks/Context:**\n- PlayerProfileProvider, usePlayerProfile, truncateAddress\n\n**Types:**\n- All major types (PlayerProfile, ProfileTransaction, GameId, etc.)\n\n**Utilities:**\n- XP calculator functions\n- Event bus functions\n- Mock simulation helpers (for testing/development)\n\n### 11. **Mock Simulation Public API**\n\nExported utilities for testing:\n- `getProfile(address)`: Retrieve stored profile\n- `getOrCreateProfile(address, forceLevel?)`: Get or create with optional level override\n- `getTransactions(address, limit)`: Get transaction history\n- `getDisplayName(address)`: Get or generate username\n- `getAvatarId(address)`: Get assigned avatar\n- `getLevel(address)`: Get player level\n- `addLoot(address, source, amount, description, gameId?, matchId?, expiresAt?)`: Award loot\n- `clearAllProfiles()`: Reset store (testing)\n- `getAllProfiles()`: Debug helper\n\n### Summary\n\nThe player-profile feature is a **complete mock-based system** that:\n1. **Stores profiles and transactions in-memory** with Maps and subscription pattern\n2. **Uses ProfileTransaction type** to track game history with outcomes and net results\n3. **Integrates with games via event bus** - games emit results, profile system records them\n4. **Provides React context API** for app-wide profile access\n5. **Includes UI components** for display (transactions table, stats grid, settings)\n6. **Auto-generates realistic mock data** for demo purposes\n7. **Uses XP formulas** to calculate levels and progression\n8. **Currently all mock** - no backend integration yet (simulated 100-300ms delays on mutations)"}],"totalDurationMs":57137,"totalTokens":64310,"totalToolUseCount":13,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7536,"cache_read_input_tokens":54632,"output_tokens":2136,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7536},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
