{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LgqpdpARA17zoWCfBSBv32","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a summary report of my findings:\n\n## Data Fetching Pattern Exploration - Findings Report\n\nI've thoroughly explored the RNG Utopia platform app to understand how API calls are made with auth headers. Here's what I found:\n\n### 1. Auth Flow Architecture\n\n**Files:**\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/context/SessionContext.tsx` - JWT session management\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/lib/auth-api.ts` - Auth endpoint wrappers\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/lib/auth-store.ts` - Token storage (localStorage + in-memory)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/main.tsx` - SessionProvider setup\n\n**Pattern:**\n- **Challenge-Response**: Wallet signs a human-readable message once → backend issues JWT tokens\n- **Token Storage**: \n  - `accessToken` + `accessExpiresAt`: in-memory only (never localStorage)\n  - `refreshToken` + `refreshExpiresAt`: persisted in localStorage\n- **Session Lifecycle**:\n  - Proactive refresh scheduled ~5 minutes before expiry\n  - Refresh mutex prevents race conditions\n  - Auto-refresh on wallet connect using existing session\n  - Manual token access via `getAccessToken()` (checks 30s buffer for expiry)\n\n### 2. How Auth Token is Accessed in Frontend\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/lib/auth-store.ts`\n\n```typescript\n// Get the current valid access token (returns null if expired)\ngetAccessToken(): string | null\n\n// Set new token (called after successful challenge-response or refresh)\nsetAccessToken(token: string, expiresAt: string): void\n```\n\n**Usage in Components:**\n- Imported directly: `import { getAccessToken } from \"../lib/auth-store\";`\n- Called at the point where the token is needed (not stored in React state to keep it secure)\n\n### 3. API Fetch Pattern with Auth Headers\n\n**Files:**\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts` (lines 509-516)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/lord-of-rngs/utils/chain.ts` (lines 658-665)\n\n**Pattern:**\n```typescript\nexport async function buildBackendCreateMatchTx(\n  creator: PublicKey,\n  amountSol: number,\n  side: CoinSide,\n  accessToken: string,  // Token passed as parameter\n): Promise<{ transaction: Transaction; ... }> {\n  const response = await fetch(getFairnessBackendCreateUrl(), {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    headers: {\n      \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\",\n      \"Authorization\": `Bearer ${accessToken}`,  // JWT Bearer scheme\n    },\n    body: JSON.stringify(payload),\n  });\n  // ... handle response\n}\n```\n\n### 4. How Existing Hooks Fetch Data\n\n**Key Hooks Found:**\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/lib/useSendAndConfirm.ts` - Transaction sending with retry logic\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/lib/useSettlementEvent.ts` - WebSocket settlement detection\n- Game context hooks in `/features/{game}/context/*.tsx`\n\n**Data Fetching Strategy:**\n- **From Chain**: Use Anchor program directly (read-only queries)\n  ```typescript\n  const account = await program.account.coinflipMatch.fetch(matchPda);\n  ```\n- **From Backend**: Use raw `fetch()` with Bearer token\n  - Backend creates signed transactions (no need for Anchor signer)\n  - Frontend fetches verification data (settlement, previous rounds)\n\n### 5. Error Handling Pattern\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/lib/parse-transaction-error.ts`\n\n**Custom Error Class:**\n- `BackendRequestError` with `.status` property (checked at lines 82-105)\n- 401 status maps to: \"Backend authentication failed. Please approve message signing and try again.\"\n- 409: conflict (retry)\n- 429: rate limit (wait and retry)\n\n**Usage in Contexts:**\n```typescript\nif (err instanceof BackendRequestError && err.status === 401) {\n  try {\n    await authenticate();  // Trigger new sign-in\n    setError(\"Session refreshed. Please try again.\");\n  } catch {\n    setError(\"Session expired. Please reconnect your wallet.\");\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### 6. Backend URL Configuration\n\n**Env Variable:**\n- `VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL` - configured in auth-api.ts and chain utils\n- Default: `http://127.0.0.1:3100`\n\n### 7. Complete Call Chain Example (Coinflip)\n\n1. **Context (`CoinflipContext.tsx`)**:\n   - Gets token: `const token = getAccessToken();`\n   - Calls: `buildBackendCreateMatchTx(publicKey, amount, side, token)`\n\n2. **Chain Utils (`chain.ts`)**:\n   - Fetches with Bearer: `fetch(url, { headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${accessToken}` } })`\n   - Parses response via `parseBackendResponse<T>()`\n\n3. **Error Handling**:\n   - Thrown errors bubble up as `BackendRequestError`\n   - Context catches, checks status code, retriggers auth if needed\n\n### Key Files Summary\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `context/SessionContext.tsx` | JWT management, challenge-response, token refresh |\n| `lib/auth-api.ts` | Raw fetch wrappers for `/auth/*` endpoints |\n| `lib/auth-store.ts` | Token storage (access in-memory, refresh in localStorage) |\n| `features/*/utils/chain.ts` | Backend API calls with Bearer token in headers |\n| `lib/parse-transaction-error.ts` | Error parsing, 401 detection |\n| `lib/useSendAndConfirm.ts` | Transaction sending (backend-signed txs don't overwrite blockhash) |\n| `lib/useSettlementEvent.ts` | WebSocket-based settlement detection (faster than polling) |\n\nThis is a clean, security-conscious pattern: tokens are never stored in React state, accessed only when needed, and the Backend Bearer scheme matches standard OAuth/JWT practices."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a42a73ab1887957c1 (use SendMessage with to: 'a42a73ab1887957c1' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 79738\ntool_uses: 33\nduration_ms: 78702</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6352b9d5-eba7-498a-a945-ee2c953d2486","uuid":"880b2e35-7a6c-41ab-b4ba-31bd2c3ae89d","timestamp":"2026-03-19T19:02:31.018Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the platform app to understand:\n1. How API calls are made with auth headers (look for fetch patterns, auth hooks, API utilities)\n2. How the auth token/JWT is accessed in frontend code\n3. How existing hooks fetch data from the backend\n4. Any existing \"useXxx\" data fetching hooks as examples\n\nLook in:\n- /workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/hooks/\n- /workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/ (look for fetch/API patterns)\n- /workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/lib/ or src/utils/ or src/api/\n- /workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/wallet/src/ (for auth context)\n\nBe thorough - I need to understand the data fetching pattern used in this project.","agentId":"a42a73ab1887957c1","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a summary report of my findings:\n\n## Data Fetching Pattern Exploration - Findings Report\n\nI've thoroughly explored the RNG Utopia platform app to understand how API calls are made with auth headers. Here's what I found:\n\n### 1. Auth Flow Architecture\n\n**Files:**\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/context/SessionContext.tsx` - JWT session management\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/lib/auth-api.ts` - Auth endpoint wrappers\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/lib/auth-store.ts` - Token storage (localStorage + in-memory)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/main.tsx` - SessionProvider setup\n\n**Pattern:**\n- **Challenge-Response**: Wallet signs a human-readable message once → backend issues JWT tokens\n- **Token Storage**: \n  - `accessToken` + `accessExpiresAt`: in-memory only (never localStorage)\n  - `refreshToken` + `refreshExpiresAt`: persisted in localStorage\n- **Session Lifecycle**:\n  - Proactive refresh scheduled ~5 minutes before expiry\n  - Refresh mutex prevents race conditions\n  - Auto-refresh on wallet connect using existing session\n  - Manual token access via `getAccessToken()` (checks 30s buffer for expiry)\n\n### 2. How Auth Token is Accessed in Frontend\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/lib/auth-store.ts`\n\n```typescript\n// Get the current valid access token (returns null if expired)\ngetAccessToken(): string | null\n\n// Set new token (called after successful challenge-response or refresh)\nsetAccessToken(token: string, expiresAt: string): void\n```\n\n**Usage in Components:**\n- Imported directly: `import { getAccessToken } from \"../lib/auth-store\";`\n- Called at the point where the token is needed (not stored in React state to keep it secure)\n\n### 3. API Fetch Pattern with Auth Headers\n\n**Files:**\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts` (lines 509-516)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/lord-of-rngs/utils/chain.ts` (lines 658-665)\n\n**Pattern:**\n```typescript\nexport async function buildBackendCreateMatchTx(\n  creator: PublicKey,\n  amountSol: number,\n  side: CoinSide,\n  accessToken: string,  // Token passed as parameter\n): Promise<{ transaction: Transaction; ... }> {\n  const response = await fetch(getFairnessBackendCreateUrl(), {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    headers: {\n      \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\",\n      \"Authorization\": `Bearer ${accessToken}`,  // JWT Bearer scheme\n    },\n    body: JSON.stringify(payload),\n  });\n  // ... handle response\n}\n```\n\n### 4. How Existing Hooks Fetch Data\n\n**Key Hooks Found:**\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/lib/useSendAndConfirm.ts` - Transaction sending with retry logic\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/lib/useSettlementEvent.ts` - WebSocket settlement detection\n- Game context hooks in `/features/{game}/context/*.tsx`\n\n**Data Fetching Strategy:**\n- **From Chain**: Use Anchor program directly (read-only queries)\n  ```typescript\n  const account = await program.account.coinflipMatch.fetch(matchPda);\n  ```\n- **From Backend**: Use raw `fetch()` with Bearer token\n  - Backend creates signed transactions (no need for Anchor signer)\n  - Frontend fetches verification data (settlement, previous rounds)\n\n### 5. Error Handling Pattern\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/lib/parse-transaction-error.ts`\n\n**Custom Error Class:**\n- `BackendRequestError` with `.status` property (checked at lines 82-105)\n- 401 status maps to: \"Backend authentication failed. Please approve message signing and try again.\"\n- 409: conflict (retry)\n- 429: rate limit (wait and retry)\n\n**Usage in Contexts:**\n```typescript\nif (err instanceof BackendRequestError && err.status === 401) {\n  try {\n    await authenticate();  // Trigger new sign-in\n    setError(\"Session refreshed. Please try again.\");\n  } catch {\n    setError(\"Session expired. Please reconnect your wallet.\");\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### 6. Backend URL Configuration\n\n**Env Variable:**\n- `VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL` - configured in auth-api.ts and chain utils\n- Default: `http://127.0.0.1:3100`\n\n### 7. Complete Call Chain Example (Coinflip)\n\n1. **Context (`CoinflipContext.tsx`)**:\n   - Gets token: `const token = getAccessToken();`\n   - Calls: `buildBackendCreateMatchTx(publicKey, amount, side, token)`\n\n2. **Chain Utils (`chain.ts`)**:\n   - Fetches with Bearer: `fetch(url, { headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${accessToken}` } })`\n   - Parses response via `parseBackendResponse<T>()`\n\n3. **Error Handling**:\n   - Thrown errors bubble up as `BackendRequestError`\n   - Context catches, checks status code, retriggers auth if needed\n\n### Key Files Summary\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `context/SessionContext.tsx` | JWT management, challenge-response, token refresh |\n| `lib/auth-api.ts` | Raw fetch wrappers for `/auth/*` endpoints |\n| `lib/auth-store.ts` | Token storage (access in-memory, refresh in localStorage) |\n| `features/*/utils/chain.ts` | Backend API calls with Bearer token in headers |\n| `lib/parse-transaction-error.ts` | Error parsing, 401 detection |\n| `lib/useSendAndConfirm.ts` | Transaction sending (backend-signed txs don't overwrite blockhash) |\n| `lib/useSettlementEvent.ts` | WebSocket-based settlement detection (faster than polling) |\n\nThis is a clean, security-conscious pattern: tokens are never stored in React state, accessed only when needed, and the Backend Bearer scheme matches standard OAuth/JWT practices."}],"totalDurationMs":78702,"totalTokens":79738,"totalToolUseCount":33,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":663,"cache_read_input_tokens":77389,"output_tokens":1683,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":663},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
