{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DSNeuUeViT7vvfkfTDwPk4","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * Thin fetch wrappers for the /auth/* backend endpoints.\n     3→ */\n     4→\n     5→const BACKEND_URL = (\n     6→  (import.meta as unknown as { env: Record<string, string | undefined> }).env\n     7→    .VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL ?? \"http://127.0.0.1:3100\"\n     8→).replace(/\\/$/, \"\");\n     9→\n    10→export interface ChallengeResponse {\n    11→  nonce: string;\n    12→  message: string;\n    13→  expiresAt: string;\n    14→}\n    15→\n    16→export interface VerifyResponse {\n    17→  accessToken: string;\n    18→  accessExpiresAt: string;\n    19→  refreshToken: string;\n    20→  refreshExpiresAt: string;\n    21→}\n    22→\n    23→export interface RefreshResponse {\n    24→  accessToken: string;\n    25→  accessExpiresAt: string;\n    26→  refreshToken: string;\n    27→  refreshExpiresAt: string;\n    28→}\n    29→\n    30→async function parseResponse<T>(res: Response): Promise<T> {\n    31→  const json = await res.json();\n    32→  if (!res.ok) {\n    33→    const msg = typeof json?.error === \"string\" ? json.error : `Auth request failed (${res.status})`;\n    34→    throw new Error(msg);\n    35→  }\n    36→  return json as T;\n    37→}\n    38→\n    39→export async function requestChallenge(wallet: string): Promise<ChallengeResponse> {\n    40→  const res = await fetch(`${BACKEND_URL}/auth/challenge`, {\n    41→    method: \"POST\",\n    42→    headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n    43→    body: JSON.stringify({ wallet }),\n    44→  });\n    45→  return parseResponse<ChallengeResponse>(res);\n    46→}\n    47→\n    48→export async function verifyChallenge(\n    49→  nonce: string,\n    50→  wallet: string,\n    51→  signature: string,\n    52→): Promise<VerifyResponse> {\n    53→  const res = await fetch(`${BACKEND_URL}/auth/verify`, {\n    54→    method: \"POST\",\n    55→    headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n    56→    body: JSON.stringify({ nonce, wallet, signature }),\n    57→  });\n    58→  return parseResponse<VerifyResponse>(res);\n    59→}\n    60→\n    61→export async function refreshSession(refreshToken: string): Promise<RefreshResponse> {\n    62→  const res = await fetch(`${BACKEND_URL}/auth/refresh`, {\n    63→    method: \"POST\",\n    64→    headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n    65→    body: JSON.stringify({ refreshToken }),\n    66→  });\n    67→  return parseResponse<RefreshResponse>(res);\n    68→}\n    69→\n    70→export async function logout(refreshToken: string): Promise<void> {\n    71→  await fetch(`${BACKEND_URL}/auth/logout`, {\n    72→    method: \"POST\",\n    73→    headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n    74→    body: JSON.stringify({ refreshToken }),\n    75→  });\n    76→}\n    77→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6352b9d5-eba7-498a-a945-ee2c953d2486","uuid":"fc9d7fad-7e02-42fc-9725-59e7be336fae","timestamp":"2026-03-19T19:02:38.718Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/lib/auth-api.ts","content":"/**\n * Thin fetch wrappers for the /auth/* backend endpoints.\n */\n\nconst BACKEND_URL = (\n  (import.meta as unknown as { env: Record<string, string | undefined> }).env\n    .VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL ?? \"http://127.0.0.1:3100\"\n).replace(/\\/$/, \"\");\n\nexport interface ChallengeResponse {\n  nonce: string;\n  message: string;\n  expiresAt: string;\n}\n\nexport interface VerifyResponse {\n  accessToken: string;\n  accessExpiresAt: string;\n  refreshToken: string;\n  refreshExpiresAt: string;\n}\n\nexport interface RefreshResponse {\n  accessToken: string;\n  accessExpiresAt: string;\n  refreshToken: string;\n  refreshExpiresAt: string;\n}\n\nasync function parseResponse<T>(res: Response): Promise<T> {\n  const json = await res.json();\n  if (!res.ok) {\n    const msg = typeof json?.error === \"string\" ? json.error : `Auth request failed (${res.status})`;\n    throw new Error(msg);\n  }\n  return json as T;\n}\n\nexport async function requestChallenge(wallet: string): Promise<ChallengeResponse> {\n  const res = await fetch(`${BACKEND_URL}/auth/challenge`, {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n    body: JSON.stringify({ wallet }),\n  });\n  return parseResponse<ChallengeResponse>(res);\n}\n\nexport async function verifyChallenge(\n  nonce: string,\n  wallet: string,\n  signature: string,\n): Promise<VerifyResponse> {\n  const res = await fetch(`${BACKEND_URL}/auth/verify`, {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n    body: JSON.stringify({ nonce, wallet, signature }),\n  });\n  return parseResponse<VerifyResponse>(res);\n}\n\nexport async function refreshSession(refreshToken: string): Promise<RefreshResponse> {\n  const res = await fetch(`${BACKEND_URL}/auth/refresh`, {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n    body: JSON.stringify({ refreshToken }),\n  });\n  return parseResponse<RefreshResponse>(res);\n}\n\nexport async function logout(refreshToken: string): Promise<void> {\n  await fetch(`${BACKEND_URL}/auth/logout`, {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n    body: JSON.stringify({ refreshToken }),\n  });\n}\n","numLines":77,"startLine":1,"totalLines":77}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_0184Lg4YJWFkGLxXd9PY6KXE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. Let me understand the API shape and the current frontend shape:\n\n**Current frontend `ProfileTransaction` type:**\n```typescript\ninterface ProfileTransaction {\n  id: string;\n  timestamp: number;\n  gameId: GameId;\n  matchId: string;\n  wagerAmount: number;\n  outcome: \"win\" | \"loss\";\n  payoutAmount: number;\n  netResult: number;\n}\n```\n\n**API response shape:**\n```json\n{\n  \"transactions\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"123\",\n      \"game\": \"coinflip\",\n      \"matchId\": \"a1b2c3d4e5f67890\",\n      \"event\": \"join\" | \"win\" | \"loss\" | \"refund\",\n      \"amountLamports\": \"5000000\",\n      \"txSig\": \"5KtP...\",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-19T12:00:00Z\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"nextCursor\": \"122\"\n}\n```\n\nI can see the mismatch now. The API uses `event` to represent transaction types (join, win, loss, refund) while the frontend currently has `outcome` with just win/loss. I need to update the `ProfileTransaction` type to include the `event` field and adjust how we map these values.\n\nFor the implementation, I'll start by creating an `ApiTransaction` type that matches the API response exactly, then update `ProfileTransaction` to use the new event field structure. Next, I'll build the `useTransactions` hook to fetch from the endpoint with proper auth and cursor support, swap out the mock function in the component, and add the load more functionality with loading states and empty handling. Each transaction row will link to the appropriate game-specific deep link based on the game type, and I'll style the event badges to distinguish between join, win, loss, and refund states. with the API data. I'm defining a clean type structure that matches what the API returns — the transaction event as a union type, and the profile transaction interface wit